body: I'm happy to look at all the mlflow/ files. Do you definitely want a separate PR for each file?
@dsgibbons Thanks for the help! I've updated the description. You can fix 1 ~ 3 items per pull request.

I'll start putting together PRs for this issue in about 12 hours @Monkero so if you want to make a start then go ahead. I'll then start fixing the ones that don't already have PRs against them, starting from the top of the list.
@harupy Would you mind saving the number of items you will fix for first-time contributors?
@Monkero Assigned the first three items to you :)
Ok, I`ve done them, but do I have to write tests for it? If the answer is 'yes', then the question is 'how?'
@Monkero No. `mlflow/pylint_plugins/set_checker.py` should work as a test.
